 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","title":"feature(web-rescale): deterministic geometry/reflow pipeline and bug eradication","description":"Goal\\n- Remove remaining web rescale/reflow bugs by making geometry transitions deterministic across container resize, DPR shifts, zoom, orientation, and font-load races.\\n\\nWhy\\n- Current bug reports and prior notes indicate multi-signal resize interactions can still produce transient corruption or drift under real browser conditions.\\n\\nScope\\n- Deterministic event ordering/coalescing across ResizeObserver, visualViewport, orientation, and explicit zoom updates.\\n- Geometry invariant enforcement from Rust/WASM core through canvas CSS/backbuffer sync.\\n- Patch baseline/reset semantics across size transitions to prevent stale diff artifacts.\\n- Regression harnesses for resize storms and pathological interleavings.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Equivalent resize/DPR/zoom/font-load traces produce identical geometry + cursor/selection outcomes.\\n- No stale-diff artifacts, garbled cells, or input-coordinate corruption under resize storms.\\n- Unit + browser E2E tests cover ordering races and pathological sequences with structured JSONL diagnostics.\\n- CI regression gates fail on geometry drift, frame hash mismatches, or missing trace evidence.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Keep host JS thin; source-of-truth geometry and invariants remain in Rust/WASM.\\n- Explicitly track and document tie-break rounding policies to avoid cross-browser divergence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","estimated_minutes":960,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:39.100971273Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:39.561849107Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dpr","fit","geometry","resize","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:39.100971273Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","title":"task(rescale): build deterministic repro corpus for reported web rescale failures","description":"Collect and codify reproducible scenarios for current rescale failures (Chrome/Safari, DPR changes, container resize storms, orientation and pinch-zoom interactions). Capture exact event timelines and expected invariants.","acceptance_criteria":"1) At least 10 deterministic rescale scenarios are captured with seeds and expected outcomes.\\n2) Each scenario records event chronology + geometry snapshots + frame hashes in JSONL.\\n3) Repro corpus is executable via scripted runner and suitable for CI.","notes":"Include direct traces around current hot paths: frankentui_showcase_demo.html resize observers and crates/frankenterm-web/src/wasm.rs fit_to_container path.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:44.584253541Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:29:35.889191410Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T06:29:29.306984044Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","repro","resize","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:44.584253541Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1183,"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"LilacBison: Created 43-test deterministic repro corpus covering 12 failure classes: fractional DPR rounding, DPR transitions, high DPR overflow, zoom×DPR multiplicative, container resize storms, orientation flips, pinch-zoom fractional values, tiny container collapse, NaN/Infinity/zero guards, exact-multiple containers, real device profiles (iPhone SE, MBP14, 4K), and monotonicity invariants. All pass, clippy clean.","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:29:35Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","title":"task(rescale): implement unified resize signal arbiter (ResizeObserver/visualViewport/orientation/zoom)","description":"Design and implement a deterministic arbiter that serializes and coalesces all resize-affecting signals into a single ordered stream with explicit tie-break rules.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Signal arbiter emits stable ordering for identical input traces.\\n2) Coalescing policy is documented and replay-test validated under burst conditions.\\n3) Unit tests cover race windows between observer callbacks, DPR change, and explicit zoom updates.","notes":"This task is the behavioral foundation for all downstream geometry fixes.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:46.217527935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:49:46.242979326Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T06:49:46.242960480Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["determinism","events","resize","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:46.217527935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:52.120015869Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1186,"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"LilacBison: Implemented ResizeArbiter in frankenterm-web/src/resize_arbiter.rs. Coalesces 7 signal types (ContainerResize, DprChange, ZoomChange, ScaleChange, DirectResize, OrientationChange, VisualViewportChange) with last-writer-wins + supersession rules. 37 tests, all 432 frankenterm-web tests pass.","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:49:40Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","title":"task(rescale): formalize font-metric invalidation + cache lifecycle on font/DPR/zoom changes","description":"Define deterministic metric invalidation boundaries and cache refresh order to prevent stale glyph metrics and geometry jumps.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Metric invalidation order is explicit and deterministic.\\n2) Unit tests cover delayed font load, swap, and fallback races.\\n3) E2E verifies absence of stale glyph artifacts after dynamic font events.","notes":"Ensure interaction with renderer scale/fit logic remains monotonic and bounded.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:47.496915903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:52.512987108Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cache","fonts","metrics","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:47.496915903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:52.512943496Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","title":"task(rescale): formalize font-metric invalidation + cache lifecycle on font/DPR/zoom changes","description":"Define deterministic metric invalidation boundaries and cache refresh order to prevent stale glyph metrics and geometry jumps.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Metric invalidation order is explicit and deterministic.\\n2) Unit tests cover delayed font load, swap, and fallback races.\\n3) E2E verifies absence of stale glyph artifacts after dynamic font events.","notes":"Ensure interaction with renderer scale/fit logic remains monotonic and bounded.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:47.496915903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:55:08.793976884Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cache","fonts","metrics","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:47.496915903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:52.512943496Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","title":"task(rescale): enforce full-repaint boundaries and diff-baseline reset across geometry transitions","description":"Guarantee that geometry-changing transitions cannot apply stale incremental diffs by enforcing full repaint boundaries and clear baseline semantics.","acceptance_criteria":"1) No stale-diff artifacts when cols/rows or pixel geometry change.\\n2) Tests validate clean behavior through rapid grow/shrink oscillations.\\n3) JSONL traces include explicit markers for baseline reset/full repaint boundaries.","notes":"Coordinate with ftui-web patch pipeline semantics and stale-diff safeguards.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:48.964268494Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:53.306774124Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diff","patches","render","resize"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:48.964268494Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:52.903164805Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:53.306720884Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","title":"task(rescale): harden pointer/mouse/touch coordinate mapping during active rescale","description":"Ensure hit-testing and input coordinate transforms stay correct while geometry changes are in-flight, including touch pinch and wheel interactions.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Input coordinates remain within valid grid bounds during/after rescale transitions.\\n2) No stuck drag/capture states due to mid-resize geometry changes.\\n3) Browser E2E covers mouse/touch/wheel interleavings with deterministic assertions.","notes":"Focus on mapping via live canvas rect + current grid with deterministic clamp policy.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:49.718415909Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:50:16.908940323Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["coordinates","input","resize","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:49.718415909Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:53.731892052Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","title":"task(rescale): harden pointer/mouse/touch coordinate mapping during active rescale","description":"Ensure hit-testing and input coordinate transforms stay correct while geometry changes are in-flight, including touch pinch and wheel interactions.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Input coordinates remain within valid grid bounds during/after rescale transitions.\\n2) No stuck drag/capture states due to mid-resize geometry changes.\\n3) Browser E2E covers mouse/touch/wheel interleavings with deterministic assertions.","notes":"Focus on mapping via live canvas rect + current grid with deterministic clamp policy.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:49.718415909Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:54:56.230984154Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T06:54:56.230965760Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["coordinates","input","resize","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:49.718415909Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:53.731892052Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1187,"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"LilacBison: Implemented CoordinateGuard in frankenterm-web/src/coordinate_guard.rs. Validated cell coordinates with exact/clamped resolution, geometry-versioned stale detection, pixel→cell and CSS→cell transforms with DPR handling. 37 tests, all 469 frankenterm-web tests pass.","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:54:51Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","title":"task(rescale-test): add browser resize-storm E2E scripts with verbose JSONL evidence","description":"Implement canonical resize-storm scripts that drive mixed resize/DPR/zoom/font events and assert geometry/frame-hash invariants.","acceptance_criteria":"1) New/updated scripts run in CI and locally with deterministic seeds.\\n2) Logs include per-event geometry snapshots, frame hashes, and failure reproduction command.\\n3) Suite catches regressions for previously observed rescale bugs.","notes":"Script outputs must be replayable and schema-stable.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:50.581107390Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:55.292676276Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","logging","resize","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:50.581107390Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:54.189593668Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:54.659801874Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:55.292634468Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.7","title":"task(rescale-diff): cross-browser differential checks for geometry and interaction parity","description":"Run deterministic scenario corpus across browser targets and compare geometry/interactions to detect browser-specific divergence early.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Differential harness reports actionable diffs with minimized repro artifacts.\\n2) Known acceptable divergences are documented with explicit rationale.\\n3) CI warns/fails on new unexplained divergence classes.","notes":"Prioritize Safari + Chromium parity for resize and DPR transitions.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:51.333439816Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:55.110874326Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["chrome","differential","firefox","safari","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:51.333439816Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:55.110815606Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","title":"task(rescale-fix): implement concrete fix set for current web rescale glitch reports","description":"Implement the concrete fix set derived from deterministic repro traces for currently observed web rescale glitches (garbled/noisy grid, transient geometry drift, stale visual state under resize/zoom/font events). This is the integration-focused fix bead bridging diagnosis to regression validation.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Reported rescale glitches are eliminated in deterministic repro corpus scenarios.\\n2) Fixes cover host orchestration + wasm geometry/fit integration boundaries as required by evidence.\\n3) Unit/integration tests guard each fixed failure mode.\\n4) Structured logs prove invariant restoration (geometry continuity, frame hash stability, interaction correctness).","notes":"Primary hotspots to evaluate and patch as needed:\\n- frankentui_showcase_demo.html resize orchestration around lines ~436-470 and ~652-665.\\n- crates/frankenterm-web/src/wasm.rs fit_to_container/set_scale/input handling around lines ~553-581 and ~626+.\\n- crates/frankenterm-web/src/wasm.rs sync_canvas_css_size around lines ~290-317.\\n- ftui-web patch baseline behavior around stale diff fallback in crates/ftui-web/src/lib.rs lines ~431-434.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:52.968559084Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:54.905810702Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bugfix","resize","showcase","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:52.968559084Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:53.724701836Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:54.104974945Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:54.487679738Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:42:54.905752813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
